html
    head
        link(rel='stylesheet', href='/stylesheet/mymain.css', type='text/css')
        
    body
        #content(style='margin-left: 300px; margin-top: 100px')
            #title(style='font-size: 150%')
                h1 API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
            #userstories
                ul(style='font-size: 150%; width: 990px')
                    li User Story: I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016).
                    li(style='margin-top: 10px') User Story: If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
                    li(style='margin-top: 10px') User Story: If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
            #examples
                h3(style='font-size: 145%') Example usage:
                p(style='color: red; font-size: 125%') https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
                p(style='color: red; margin-top: -20px; font-size: 125%') https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600
            #examples
                h3(style='font-size: 145%') Example output:
                p(style='color: red; font-size: 125%') { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }
    